Project #1: Stoke Data¶

Divya Murala

  • In this project, stroke data is being explored. There a number of factors that affect the risk of a stroke and through this project the goal is to understand which specific factors contribut the most to the risk of a stroke by analysis both medicaa and social factors.

  • KNN Classification, Random Forest and Logistic Regression was employed to predict the risk of an individual having a storke. Both numerical and categorical feautres were taken into account to predict.

  • Source: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/fedesoriano/stroke-prediction-dataset/data

#Standardization 

numerical = ['age','bmi','avg_glucose_level']
categorical = ['gender', 'ever_married', 'work_type', 'Residence_type', 'smoking_status']

df_numerical = df[numerical]
df_categorical = df[categorical]

df_encoded_categorical = pd.get_dummies(df_categorical, drop_first=True)
df_encoded = pd.concat([df_numerical, df_encoded_categorical], axis=1)

In [17]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

k_values = list(range(1, 31))  
best_k = None
best_accuracy = 0
accuracies = []

for k in k_values:
    knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=k)
    knn.fit(X_train_resampled, y_train_resampled)
    y_pred_test = knn.predict(X_test)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_test)
    accuracies.append(accuracy)

    if accuracy > best_accuracy:
        best_accuracy = accuracy
        best_k = k

print(f"Best K for KNN: {best_k}")
print(f"Test Accuracy: {best_accuracy:.2f}")

Best K for KNN: 2
Test Accuracy: 0.88

from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve, average_precision_score, roc_curve, roc_auc_score  # Add this import

# KNN Classification: ROC and AUC Curve
y_prob_train = knn.predict_proba(X_train_resampled)[:, 1]
y_prob_test = knn.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

# Calculate ROC curves
fpr_train, tpr_train, thresholds_train = roc_curve(y_train_resampled, y_prob_train)
fpr_test, tpr_test, thresholds_test = roc_curve(y_test, y_prob_test)

# Calculate AUC values
roc_auc_train = roc_auc_score(y_train_resampled, y_prob_train)
roc_auc_test = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob_test)

# Plot ROC Curves
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(fpr_train, tpr_train, color='darkorange', lw=2, label=f'Train ROC Curve (AUC = {roc_auc_train:.2f})')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='gray', linestyle='--')
plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate (FPR)')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate (TPR)')
plt.title('Train ROC Curve')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.plot(fpr_test, tpr_test, color='darkorange', lw=2, label=f'Test ROC Curve (AUC = {roc_auc_test:.2f})')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='gray', linestyle='--')
plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])  # Corrected line
plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate (FPR)')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate (TPR)')
plt.title('Test ROC Curve')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve, average_precision_score, roc_curve, roc_auc_score
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Calculate Precision-Recall curves using the same datasets
precision_train, recall_train, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_train_resampled, y_prob_train)
precision_test, recall_test, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_test, y_prob_test)

# Calculate Average Precision using the same datasets
average_precision_train = average_precision_score(y_train_resampled, y_prob_train)
average_precision_test = average_precision_score(y_test, y_prob_test)

# Create two separate subplots for training and test Precision-Recall curves side by side
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))

# Training Precision-Recall curve
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(recall_train, precision_train, color='darkorange', lw=2, label=f'Train Avg. Precision = {average_precision_train:.2f}')
plt.xlabel('Recall')
plt.ylabel('Precision')
plt.title('Train Precision-Recall Curve')
plt.legend(loc='lower left')

# Test Precision-Recall curve
plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.plot(recall_test, precision_test, color='darkorange', lw=2, label=f'Test Avg. Precision = {average_precision_test:.2f}')
plt.xlabel('Recall')
plt.ylabel('Precision')
plt.title('Test Precision-Recall Curve')
plt.legend(loc='lower left')

plt.tight_layout()
